  <description><![CDATA[<h2>Explore Switzerland's diverse scenery with two contrasting regions easily connected by train</h2>
<p>Combining contrasting regions of Lake Geneva in south-western <a data-udi="umb://document/92803bd348ec48c1b64d53e77931172d" href="/{localLink:umb://document/92803bd348ec48c1b64d53e77931172d}" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>, and the <a data-udi="umb://document/d1bb27ef1cf04b448d45b9dcbfeb2771" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d1bb27ef1cf04b448d45b9dcbfeb2771}" title="Bernese Oberland">Bernese Oberland</a>, you'll discover some of the most beautiful landscapes in Switzerland on this popular multi-centre holiday.</p>
<p>December 2022 was an important month in the history of this train line, with the launch of the GoldenPass Express. This train connects two equally popular regions. Both offering trips around the lakes or hikes into surrounding mountains. You can enjoy new carriages with panoramic windows and comfortable seating between <a data-udi="umb://document/c98b896d425a4f9eb1d5e2464d2c17c2" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c98b896d425a4f9eb1d5e2464d2c17c2}" title="Montreux">Montreux</a> and  <a data-udi="umb://document/7456bae57241449a84a68959b62b2aba" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7456bae57241449a84a68959b62b2aba}" title="Interlaken">Interlaken</a>  without changing train at Zweisimmen. Two tracks meet here and an ingenious and innovative technical development has modified the gauge of the bogies and the height of the carriages in relation to the platform as they pass through Zweisimmen station. This means you stay on board and travel directly between your two destinations.</p>
<h3>Guide price from: £1,760pp*</h3>
<h3>Your multi-centre holiday options: </h3>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>Flexible durations in each destination</li>
<li>Travel and change destination on a Wednesday, Friday or Saturday</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h3>Your holiday includes:</h3>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>Return flights or trains from the UK</li>
<li>2nd class train transfers from the airport to your hotel in Montreux, from your hotel in Montreux to your hotel in Interlaken and from your hotel in Interlaken to the airport (some changes of trains required, 1st class upgrade possible at extra cost)</li>
<li>Option to include travel on the Golden Pass Panoramic Train between Montreux and Interlaken with seat reservation* (if you prefer, you can opt not to include travel on the Golden Pass Train, in which case your transfer will be by standard train and may require a change of trains along the route)</li>
<li>Swiss Half Fare Card - worth over £100 – included as part of your rail tickets</li>
<li>Accommodation in your chosen hotel in each destination</li>
<li>Unlimited use of local buses in Montreux and Interlaken with local guest cards (provided by your hotels)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><em>*Please note that we will organise seat reservations for you on the Golden Pass Express but while we will try our very best to arrange seats together, due to huge demand on the services, we can’t guarantee this.</em></p>
<p> </p>
